'RATED
  I ordered from the Navratra Menu during Navratri this month. Out of the wide variety offered I ordered the Sabudana Vada and Curd meal and Kuttu Aloo Parantha with Paneer Makhanwala Royal Meal.

The Sabudana Vada was perfectly made and was a great light meal paired with curd. The Kutti Aloo Paratha and Paneer Makhanwala Royal Meal was a great combination. Making aloo paratha with Kuttu is a great idea and it tasted amazing. The meal also included a portion of curd and a portion of Hare Tamatar ki Sabzi.

The overall experience of ordering food from here was excellent as the food was delivered fresh and on time with good packing to avoid spills and leaks.

""RATED
  If you are looking for value for money then this is NOT the place to go to. Usually places that charge exorbitant prices for the usual food items offer food of superior quality! But that is not the case here at Kailash Parbat. This is my second such experience. The veg Thali came at a high price ( of course!) But quantity wise it was decent. The food definitely looks good but it fails to blow your mind in terms of taste.
The rice that came with the combo was extremely bland. It felt like they just mixed vegetables and cooked rice for the heck of it! The saving grace of the whole meal was the dal and the Boondi raita. The Chana and Paneer weren't impressive either. The size of the gulab jamun that came in this meal was the size of a pebble.
The only other refreshing part of the meal was the buttermilk. Nice consistency and satisfactory taste.

Paisa Vasool? Not really.

thechubgrubsandtravels.blogspot.com"")

name:
'RATED
  || Sunday Night ||

Vapour is one of my favourite place in Bangalore.

Ambience: The rooftop ambience is great. People can enjoy cool breeze and chill and relax. It was not much crowded as it was Sunday Night.

Staff/Service: The staff and their service are both very quick. No complains on this aspect.

Food/Beverages: In food we ordered Chicken Piccata along with Chilli Chicken. Both were great. Chicken Piccata was very Cripsy and the Chilli Chicken just melted in the mouth. Loved it. In beverages we took Blonde Beer and Cosmopolitini. The Beer was smooth and the Cosmopolitini just stole my heart.

This was my second visit to Vapour Indiranagar and I am looking forward to many more happy visits.

online_order:
'RATED
  Pump house in jp nagar is the most happening place and also the talk of the town.

Ambience - Damn this place is huge and also inside the heart of the city. The place is lit and always buzzing with people. They have one of the coolest lighting to offer. Two big huge fans cover the entire ceiling which looks great. Then it also has both indoor and outdoor seating.

Food - Coming to the food we ordered the nachos and it was crispy and tasty with spicy touch also with cheese and salsa. The taste was damn good. Then was the kasundi paneer tikka which was very soft panner charred with mix of sauce. The paneer was fresh and very good. The arrabiatta pizza was good but no spiciness and also was bland with only tomatoes and a lot of garlic. Then we ordered the penne red sauce pasta which was good but not upto the mark.

Parking - Valet parking is available

Food - 4/5
Service - 4/5
Ambience - 5/5
Price - 4/5

Happy fooding.')
